  "texts": [
    "Each sensor node, i, initializes a local model, θi, with the same architecture as the global model.",
    "The local datasets Xi and labels Yi remain on the sensor nodes to preserve data privacy.During each communication round, the sensor nodes update their local models using the current global model and their respective local datasets.",
    "The updated models, θi(t), are then sent to the cloud server for aggregation.",
    "The cloud server aggregates the model updates from all nodes to create an updated global model, θg(t).",
    "This global model reflects the collective knowledge of all sensor nodes while preserving data privacy."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}